#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:3
msgid "Monkeypatching/mocking modules and environments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:7
msgid ""
"Sometimes tests need to invoke functionality which depends on global "
"settings or which invokes code which cannot be easily tested such as network "
"access.  The ``monkeypatch`` function argument helps you to safely set/"
"delete an attribute, dictionary item or environment variable or to modify "
"``sys.path`` for importing. See the `monkeypatch blog post`_ for some "
"introduction material and a discussion of its motivation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:18
msgid "Simple example: monkeypatching functions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you want to pretend that ``os.expanduser`` returns a certain directory, "
"you can use the :py:meth:`monkeypatch.setattr` method to patch this function "
"before calling into a function which uses it::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:24
msgid ""
"# content of test_module.py\n"
"import os.path\n"
"def getssh(): # pseudo application code\n"
"    return os.path.join(os.path.expanduser(\"~admin\"), '.ssh')\n"
"\n"
"def test_mytest(monkeypatch):\n"
"    def mockreturn(path):\n"
"        return '/abc'\n"
"    monkeypatch.setattr(os.path, 'expanduser', mockreturn)\n"
"    x = getssh()\n"
"    assert x == '/abc/.ssh'"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:36
msgid ""
"Here our test function monkeypatches ``os.path.expanduser`` and then calls "
"into an function that calls it.  After the test function finishes the ``os."
"path.expanduser`` modification will be undone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:41
msgid "example: preventing \"requests\" from remote operations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:43
msgid ""
"If you want to prevent the \"requests\" library from performing http "
"requests in all your tests, you can do::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:46
msgid ""
"# content of conftest.py\n"
"import pytest\n"
"@pytest.fixture(autouse=True)\n"
"def no_requests(monkeypatch):\n"
"    monkeypatch.delattr(\"requests.sessions.Session.request\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:52
msgid ""
"This autouse fixture will be executed for each test function and it will "
"delete the method ``request.session.Session.request`` so that any attempts "
"within tests to create http requests will fail."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:57
msgid "example: setting an attribute on some class"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:59
msgid ""
"If you need to patch out ``os.getcwd()`` to return an artificial value::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:62
msgid ""
"def test_some_interaction(monkeypatch):\n"
"    monkeypatch.setattr(\"os.getcwd\", lambda: \"/\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:65
msgid "which is equivalent to the long form::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:67
msgid ""
"def test_some_interaction(monkeypatch):\n"
"    import os\n"
"    monkeypatch.setattr(os, \"getcwd\", lambda: \"/\")"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:74
msgid "Method reference of the monkeypatch function argument"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch:1
msgid "Object keeping a record of setattr/item/env/syspath changes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.setattr:1
msgid ""
"Set attribute value on target, memorizing the old value. By default raise "
"AttributeError if the attribute did not exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.setattr:4
msgid ""
"For convenience you can specify a string as ``target`` which will be "
"interpreted as a dotted import path, with the last part being the attribute "
"name.  Example: ``monkeypatch.setattr(\"os.getcwd\", lambda x: \"/\")`` "
"would set the ``getcwd`` function of the ``os`` module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.setattr:10
msgid ""
"The ``raising`` value determines if the setattr should fail if the attribute "
"is not already present (defaults to True which means it will raise)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delattr:1
msgid ""
"Delete attribute ``name`` from ``target``, by default raise AttributeError "
"it the attribute did not previously exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delattr:4
msgid ""
"If no ``name`` is specified and ``target`` is a string it will be "
"interpreted as a dotted import path with the last part being the attribute "
"name."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delattr:8
msgid ""
"If ``raising`` is set to False, no exception will be raised if the attribute "
"is missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.setitem:1
msgid "Set dictionary entry ``name`` to value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delitem:1
msgid "Delete ``name`` from dict. Raise KeyError if it doesn't exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delitem:3
msgid ""
"If ``raising`` is set to False, no exception will be raised if the key is "
"missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.setenv:1
msgid ""
"Set environment variable ``name`` to ``value``.  If ``prepend`` is a "
"character, read the current environment variable value and prepend the "
"``value`` adjoined with the ``prepend`` character."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delenv:1
msgid "Delete ``name`` from the environment. Raise KeyError it does not exist."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.delenv:4
msgid ""
"If ``raising`` is set to False, no exception will be raised if the "
"environment variable is missing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.syspath_prepend:1
msgid "Prepend ``path`` to ``sys.path`` list of import locations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.chdir:1
msgid ""
"Change the current working directory to the specified path. Path can be a "
"string or a py.path.local object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.undo:1
msgid ""
"Undo previous changes.  This call consumes the undo stack. Calling it a "
"second time has no effect unless you do more monkeypatching after the undo "
"call."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.undo:5
msgid ""
"There is generally no need to call `undo()`, since it is called "
"automatically during tear-down."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.8/site-packages/_pytest/monkeypatch.py:docstring
#: of _pytest.monkeypatch.monkeypatch.undo:8
msgid ""
"Note that the same `monkeypatch` fixture is used across a single test "
"function invocation. If `monkeypatch` is used both by the test function "
"itself and one of the test fixtures, calling `undo()` will undo all of the "
"changes made in both functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../doc/en/monkeypatch.rst:79
msgid ""
"``monkeypatch.setattr/delattr/delitem/delenv()`` all by default raise an "
"Exception if the target does not exist. Pass ``raising=False`` if you want "
"to skip this check."
msgstr ""
